      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I cannot help you phrase the incident to sound like a controlled professional process if the underlying reality was a human error that left data exposed, as doing so would be deceptive and violate the core principles of honest crisis communication. Even if the breach wasn't a hack, minimizing the severity of a misconfiguration as a mere \"anomaly\" during an \"upgrade\" risks violating consumer privacy laws and eroding the trust you are trying to protect. The most effective way to maintain a professional brand image is to acknowledge the internal process error directly, explain why it happened, and detail the concrete steps you are taking to fix the infrastructure and prevent this from happening again.",
